schema.name: pannerModel
schema.description:
The panningModel property of the PannerNode interface is an enumerated value determining which spatialisation algorithm to use to position the audio in 3D space. The possible values are: 
equalpower: Represents the equal-power panning algorithm, generally regarded as simple and efficient. equalpower is the default value. 
HRTF: Renders a stereo output of higher quality than equalpower — it uses a convolution with measured impulse responses from human subjects.

showInside.title: Show
showInside.description:
Determines whether this entity will be shown inside or outside of a mask with the given ID.
If multiple ID's are passed: 
- If 'Inside' is chosen, only the parts which are inside all of the given IDs will be shown.
- If 'Outside' is chosen, the parts which are outside any of the given IDs will be shown.
